Description:
Do you want to work in a front-end development position?
Are you a great TypeScript developer?
Your primary focus will be developing user interface components using React, Material-UI and Jest.




 If you are ticking all these boxes, then look at the spec below for your next career move:




Work as part of the Development team in a front-end capacity;
Build reusable components and libraries that can be used across multiple products within the company eco-system;
Develop high performance microfront-end systems utilizing TypeScript, React, Material-UI and the single-spa framework;
Implement unit tests using the Jest framework;
Developing new user interfaces for a new InProgress product on an internal UI Library using HTML5, CSS3, SASS and Semantic UI;
The ideal candidate will make continuous improvements and have specific input into the design and architecture of both current and future products;
Collaborating with a team of creative and technical experts, providing input on activities ranging from tactical projects to significant architectural and user interface improvements;
Contributing to the entire development lifecycle from initial concept creation through to planning, implementation. The aim is to produce well designed, properly structured, high quality and high performing software on schedule.




Degree in Computer Science, Data Science or relevant
3+ years of relevant work experience
Highly proficient in both Typescript, React and its ecosystem
Practical working knowledge in HTML5, CSS3, SASS using Semantic UI
Practical working knowledge of some of the following: React Hooks, single-spa, Jest
Results orientated with a high degree of accountability and responsibility
Flexible to changing requirements while managing an own task list and time
Team player with the ability to take ownership of responsibility of the team’s success
Full stack back-end knowledge, e.g. C#, SQL on distributed systems would be a plus

Contract role - Dublin/Remote - June/July Kick off

Technology is empowering every person and every organization on the planet to do more and achieve more. Our culture is centred on embracing a growth mindset, a theme of inspiring excellence and encouraging individuals, teams and leaders to bring their best each day.

Client Solutions is a leading Irish technology services business founded in 1994 with offices in Dublin, Cork, Barcelona and Wroclaw. We combine our team of experts with cutting-edge technologies to provide a broad range of valuable business solutions to help our clients maximise their performance and achieve their goals. We are privileged to have many of Ireland’s blue-chip companies as clients across our key market sectors, Financial, Telecommunications, Life Sciences, Retail/Distribution, Manufacturing and key departments in the Public Sector.

We are currently recruiting for a C#.Net Software Developer, to take up a long term contract - working with microsoft stack technologies from C# to SQL and Azure. 

Experience with writing and consuming Web APIs would be beneficial.

Requirements

Knowledge, Skills & Experience

 Highly effective/Advanced Software development skills with 5 years+ experience in
 Typescript / JavaScript / C#;
 Commercial experience in Angular(8+);


Essential experience with:

 writing and consuming Web APIs;
 .NET and .NET Core;
 SOLID design principles;
 GOF design patterns;
 Common Data Structures and Algorithms;


Candidates Should also have:

 5+ years of Unit Testing in C# using MSTest
 Angular testing using Jasmine and Karma;
 knowledge of SQL Server development;
 Code review experience;
 Some UX design experience would beneficial;
 Some experience of Waterfall, Agile or Iterative development
 Experience with Agile and Continuous delivery / DevOps
 An ability to write and unit test code to a given specification


Benefits

This project kicks off at the end of May. Candidates should be ready to start at the end of May or early June at the latest. Please do not apply if you are not available from the dates mentioned. This is a contract role and as such no visa or work permit is offered or implied.

The Company




EXADS is a young international software startup specialising in adtech. In business since 2013, EXADS is a self-sufficient, well funded and privately owned company with offices in Dublin and Porto. We are part of EXOGROUP, a set of companies made up of 150+ talents and offering a wide range of services within the digital business landscape with headquarters in Barcelona and offices in Dublin, Porto, Valencia, Madrid, Tarragona and Buenos Aires.




As a company, we actively develop and maintain our own proprietary ad-serving technology platform and custom-built infrastructure enabling us to innovate and deploy new features and functionality quickly in a fast-moving and demanding industry.




We are revolutionising the online ad-serving industry for advertisers, publishers and networks alike and are seeking to recruit highly skilled and talented Senior Backend Developers to join our dedicated development team in Porto to further design, build and scale our platform offerings across a wide range of web and mobile projects which utilise cutting edge technologies such as Big Data and Real Time Statistics Computation.




The ideal candidate will have a passion for open-source software and enjoy working in a fast-paced, challenging but rewarding environment.




Responsibilities: 

Development of modular, testable and scalable software components for core platform and Web services / APIs;
Code optimisations for performance and scalability. Maintenance / refactoring of legacy systems;
Research and development of new and emerging technologies;
Contribute to team processes improvement adhering to industry best practices and principles;
Participate in regular code reviews and team knowledge sharing activities.




Skills and Experience: 

5+ years experience in object-oriented PHP development (preferably PHP 7+);
Solid foundation in SQL databases and design, specifically MariaDB;
Experience with caching tools and techniques (APC, Memcached);
Capable of building server-side and client-side applications with PHP, Javascript, HTML;
Strong knowledge about design patterns, security and performance concepts;
Good understanding of RESTful architecture;
Knowledge of Git / Github and related workflows in a distributed team environment;
Experience with Go is a plus;
Excellent written, spoken and interpersonal communication skills (English and Portuguese).




Education & Qualifications: 




BS/MS in Computer Science / related technical discipline OR equivalent experience 




What we offer:

We offer a position in a young, dynamic and international environment and the opportunity for permanent training, personal development, ambitious career growth and a competitive salary based on experience.




Most of all, we offer a position in a team that thrives on achievement, success and leadership within our industry. Our core company value is innovation: where people and creativity drive innovative technology. If you have a passion for open-source software and enjoy working in a fast-paced, challenging but rewarding environment, this position is for you! 




Company benefits:




Flexible start times - Health insurance - Your Birthday off as a paid holiday - Udemy learning - EXOGROUP University, our in-house training - Employee referral program bonus - Off-site team building days out - Fresh fruit - Friday team breakfast - Meal card - Team Lunches - Possibility to work full remote anywhere around Portugal 




